You wanna go downtown, Bernie? Huh?

31:48.499 --> 31:50.933
Impound you van, explain your daily activities?

31:51.002 --> 31:52.700
You remember the last time.

31:52.726 --> 31:54.485
Okay, I... Shit! Okay.

31:59.643 --> 32:02.087
I want the Engineer, Bernie.

32:02.113 --> 32:03.160
Who is he?

32:03.213 --> 32:04.259
I never met him.

32:04.285 --> 32:05.305
I swear to God.

32:05.331 --> 32:06.832
I just heard stories.

32:08.184 --> 32:10.152
<i>This guy Terry,</i>

32:10.219 --> 32:13.484
he used to run women for the Engineer.

32:13.556 --> 32:17.924
A few years back the Engineer sends Terry this new girl.

32:17.992 --> 32:20.859
<i>Terry</i>...
<i>poor bastard</i>...

32:20.929 --> 32:24.330
pulls up his pants one day and finds out he's in love.

32:24.399 --> 32:26.924
<i>Well, they decide they're gonna get married. </i>

32:27.001 --> 32:29.434
But the Engineer said no.

32:31.405 --> 32:33.339
So Terry just takes her away.

32:33.407 --> 32:34.720
I mean, they elope.

32:34.746 --> 32:38.131
They go hide out in this cabin up in the hills.

32:38.178 --> 32:41.305
<i>They were gonna start this whole new fucking life together. </i>

32:41.380 --> 32:43.712
Then one day...

32:43.783 --> 32:46.217
Terry came home and...

32:46.285 --> 32:48.310
She was just gone.

32:51.289 --> 32:53.223
Terry went crazy.

32:53.291 --> 32:55.851
He put the word out on the street.

32:55.927 --> 32:58.953
<i>He said, "I'm gonna find the Engineer
and take back what's mine. "</i>

32:59.030 --> 33:02.795
Hunt for the Engineer and the Engineer hunts you.

33:02.867 --> 33:04.960
What did you say?

33:06.337 --> 33:09.204
Nothing.
It's just this...

33:09.273 --> 33:12.003
When people...

33:12.076 --> 33:14.009
hunt for the Engineer,

33:14.077 --> 33:16.011
they say...

33:16.079 --> 33:18.013
then the Engineer will hunt you.

33:23.753 --> 33:25.686
So then what happened?

33:26.889 --> 33:29.323
<i>Terry kept looking,</i>

33:29.391 --> 33:33.987
<i>but he never found the Engineer and to this
day he's never seen the Engineer again. </i>

33:34.062 --> 33:35.995
<i>But... </i>

33:36.063 --> 33:38.497
<i>Terry started getting these gifts,</i>

33:38.566 --> 33:41.831
<i>like the Engineer was sending him a message. </i>

33:41.903 --> 33:44.838
<i>A box would show up on his doorstep,</i>

33:44.906 --> 33:46.778
<i>or something would come in the mail...</i>

33:46.804 --> 33:48.195
<i>a locket that she once wore,</i>

33:48.241 --> 33:51.301
<i>or a clump of her hair. </i>

33:51.378 --> 33:53.312
<i>When her wedding ring arrived,</i>

33:53.380 --> 33:55.314
<i>Terry figured that she was dead. </i>

33:55.382 --> 33:57.942
<i>But he kept looking. </i>

33:58.017 --> 34:01.077
<i>And then just as it happened when she disappeared,</i>

34:01.153 --> 34:04.020
<i>Terry came home one morning and she was back again,</i>

34:04.089 --> 34:07.024
<i>just laying there in his bed, sleeping like a little baby. </i>

34:09.360 --> 34:12.295
<i>He tiptoed over to the bed... </i>

34:12.362 --> 34:15.297
<i>so he could slide in next to her. </i>

34:17.135 --> 34:19.295
<i>He pulled back the covers,</i>

34:20.603 --> 34:22.538
<i>but she wasn't there. </i>

34:23.774 --> 34:26.208
<i>What do you mean, she wasn't</i>...

34:27.444 --> 34:30.379
<i> Just a note where her body should have been. </i>

34:32.014 --> 34:33.606
<i>It said:</i>

34:35.717 --> 34:37.811
"You win, Terry.

34:37.887 --> 34:39.447
I kept what I needed.

34:39.474 --> 34:41.109
The rest is yours. "

34:46.194 --> 34:47.752
You believe that story?

34:47.829 --> 34:49.505
I saw his face when he told me.

34:49.532 --> 34:51.152
Terry wouldn't make that up.

34:51.199 --> 34:53.292
You talk to Terry.

34:53.368 --> 34:55.110
I don't talk to the guy anymore.

34:55.136 --> 34:56.987
I don't know where he is... Aah!

34:57.036 --> 34:59.972
You talk to him.

35:00.040 --> 35:03.407
By the end of the day I wanna know where I can find the Engineer.

35:10.883 --> 35:12.908
<i> You get anything from the ice cream man?</i>

35:14.153 --> 35:15.631
Any information, I mean.

35:15.657 --> 35:17.010
What's up, Tony?

35:17.055 --> 35:19.216
What's bothering you?

35:20.592 --> 35:22.526
I just...

35:22.594 --> 35:26.928
I just think there's some lines you set, and you don't cross 'em.

35:26.999 --> 35:28.932
Period.

35:29.000 --> 35:32.766
Otherwise you just keep crossin' 'em one after another, you know,

35:32.837 --> 35:35.271
until you're just lost.

35:35.339 --> 35:37.273
We're partners.

35:37.341 --> 35:38.102
And that matters.

35:38.128 --> 35:39.424
That means something to me.

35:39.476 --> 35:41.410
But I can't do this, Joe.

35:43.380 --> 35:45.610
I'm gonna tell the captain about Daphne,

35:45.682 --> 35:48.116
<i>about wipin' your prints off. </i>

35:48.184 --> 35:50.674
<i>I'm gonna tell him what we did. </i>

35:52.421 --> 35:54.787
I believe you didn't kill that girl.

35:54.857 --> 35:56.791
Tell him with me.

35:56.859 --> 36:00.158
<i>It's the right thing to do. </i>

36:00.229 --> 36:04.358
Well, you're right about one thing, Tony.

36:04.432 --> 36:07.060
I didn't kill that girl.

36:07.135 --> 36:11.003
And I'm not gonna let anything get in the way of me finding out who did.

36:15.275 --> 36:17.709
Where's your pen?

36:19.780 --> 36:21.714
Your pen.

36:21.782 --> 36:23.610
The one with your initials on it.

36:23.636 --> 36:25.139
The one your wife gave you.

36:26.185 --> 36:27.675
I don't know.

36:29.955 --> 36:30.675
That's right.

36:30.701 --> 36:32.915
It's probably at the crime lab by now.

36:32.958 --> 36:34.580
Forensics picked it up.

36:34.606 --> 36:36.509
You left it at the scene.

36:36.561 --> 36:40.361
<i>And that last pack of cigarettes you smoked,</i>

36:40.432 --> 36:43.367
the one with your fingerprints all over the wrapper...

36:43.435 --> 36:45.835
You left your smokes there too, Tony.

36:45.904 --> 36:48.303
- You took my cigarettes?
- <i>No. </i>

36:48.372 --> 36:49.152
No, no, no.

36:49.178 --> 36:51.093
You came to me, remember?

36:51.141 --> 36:52.631
- I what?
- <i>Yeah. </i>

36:52.710 --> 36:54.803
Yeah, 'cause you fucked some whore...

36:54.878 --> 36:57.812
and, holy shit, found her dead the next morning.

36:57.880 --> 37:01.680
You asked me to help you wipe the place clean, cover your tracks.

37:01.751 --> 37:04.276
I should never have done it,

37:04.353 --> 37:07.720
but as anyone knows, I am nothing if not a loyal partner.

37:07.790 --> 37:10.656
<i>You have two years in the precinct. </i>

37:10.726 --> 37:13.661
Now, who do you think they're gonna believe, me or you?

37:13.729 --> 37:16.220
Especially considering all the evidence.

37:16.298 --> 37:18.232
You fuckin' scumbag.

37:18.300 --> 37:19.131
You planned it?

37:19.157 --> 37:21.259
You fucked me, and you planned this?

37:21.302 --> 37:24.567
<i>No. </i>
<i>Nobody is gonna get fucked. </i>

37:24.638 --> 37:27.072
You see,
that is the beauty of it.

37:27.141 --> 37:29.939
When the crime lab files its report,

37:30.010 --> 37:33.570
<i>I'll tell the captain that you were
shaken up by what we found at the scene. </i>

37:33.646 --> 37:37.776
I saw you have a smoke and touch a few
things before you put on the gloves.

37:37.851 --> 37:39.238
<i>It's a simple mistake.</i>

37:39.264 --> 37:42.539
<i>The worst you're gonna get is a verbal reprimand. </i>

37:42.588 --> 37:45.523
I don't want to make you look bad.

37:45.591 --> 37:47.525
I'll take care of you.

37:48.694 --> 37:50.787
Just gotta cover my ass, that's all.

37:52.865 --> 37:54.798
And I trusted you.

38:11.681 --> 38:13.234
Detective Thorne?

38:13.260 --> 38:14.903
This is for you.

38:44.912 --> 38:49.349
Stop. Please stop.

38:49.416 --> 38:51.349
No more. No. No!

39:05.697 --> 39:08.097
<i>Please! Please!</i>

40:02.382 --> 40:05.249
This...

40:06.887 --> 40:08.854
I don't
understand this.

40:08.921 --> 40:12.982
<i>Can you run a test on the videotape to see if it's been erased?</i>

40:13.058 --> 40:16.186
I can tell if it's been erased, but I can't
tell you what was on it before that,

40:16.262 --> 40:18.492
if anything.

40:18.564 --> 40:19.922
I know what was on it.

40:19.948 --> 40:21.182
I know what I saw.

40:21.232 --> 40:25.259
<i> Joseph, we've already been through the entire tape twice. </i>

40:25.336 --> 40:26.895
- <i>There's nothing there. </i>

40:26.921 --> 40:28.728
- I saw what I fucking saw!

40:29.807 --> 40:31.433
<i>Gentlemen, let's move on. </i>

40:31.508 --> 40:33.442
We all have
work to do.

40:33.510 --> 40:36.343
Joseph, if you could stay here a moment, please.

40:38.482 --> 40:40.541
<i>I'm concerned about your state of mind. </i>

40:40.617 --> 40:42.243
Bernie's your snitch, right?

40:42.318 --> 40:44.343
<i>Was</i> my snitch.

40:44.420 --> 40:47.583
And you knew the first victim, Jay Cho.

40:47.657 --> 40:49.179
I barely knew him.

40:49.205 --> 40:50.810
It was years ago.

40:50.860 --> 40:53.596
My instincts keep telling me something's not right here.

40:53.622 --> 40:54.581
I'm very concerned.

40:54.629 --> 40:56.563
<i>Now, I could suspend you,</i>

40:56.631 --> 40:59.099
but I won't do that.

40:59.167 --> 41:03.001
However, I will make a formal request that you see the department counselor.

41:03.071 --> 41:04.886
I don't have time for that, Captain.

41:04.912 --> 41:06.531
There's a child's life at stake.

41:06.573 --> 41:08.041
All the more reason.

41:08.067 --> 41:09.533
It's not optional.

41:09.576 --> 41:13.444
<i>Now, go make an appointment before
you do any more work on this case. </i>

41:19.485 --> 41:22.420
Expect to see me come out in handcuffs?

41:22.488 --> 41:25.582
No. Why?
Did you do somethin' bad?

41:34.633 --> 41:36.601
<i>Leon Gaultier. </i>

41:36.668 --> 41:39.295
His fingerprints were on the box.

41:39.370 --> 41:41.270
The box?

41:41.339 --> 41:44.103
<i>The one at the Jay Cho crime scene. </i>

41:44.175 --> 41:46.109
It was under the candle.

41:46.177 --> 41:48.111
<i> Jay stole it from Leon. </i>

41:48.179 --> 41:50.476
Thanks for keepin' me informed, partner.

41:50.547 --> 41:52.481
I'm telling you, Tony,

41:52.549 --> 41:55.484
I saw the murder weapon, the one that killed Bernie.

41:55.552 --> 41:58.077
It was on the wall at Leon's shop.

41:58.154 --> 42:01.088
What, the whip on the videotape?

42:03.158 --> 42:05.149
<i> Just find Leon... </i>

42:05.227 --> 42:07.161
and pick him up, okay?

42:07.229 --> 42:09.390
And keep an eye out for Bernie's van.

42:09.416 --> 42:10.951
What are you gonna do?

42:13.001 --> 42:15.936
I'm gonna go lie down and talk about my childhood.

42:18.006 --> 42:22.466
<i>So, were you involved in the use of deadly force?</i>

42:22.543 --> 42:24.476
Not lately.

42:25.846 --> 42:28.007
Substance problems?

42:28.081 --> 42:28.902
- <i>Problems at home?</i>

42:28.928 --> 42:30.870
- Didn't the captain tell you why I'm here?

42:32.419 --> 42:34.648
No.
Why are you here?

42:34.720 --> 42:38.986
Well, not because I want to be.

42:39.058 --> 42:40.992
Please sit down.

42:44.030 --> 42:46.277
These sessions are informal.

42:46.303 --> 42:49.754
We can just talk about anything you like.

42:49.801 --> 42:51.089
- <i>That's a nice picture. </i>

42:51.115 --> 42:52.659
- <i>It's my daughter Melissa. </i>

42:52.704 --> 42:54.865
- She's six.
- I have a little girl too.

42:54.939 --> 42:57.168
She's gonna be nine in about a month.

42:57.241 --> 42:59.732
So I take it you're not a priest?

42:59.810 --> 43:02.074
Episcopal.

43:02.146 --> 43:04.080
We get to have a little fun.

43:05.682 --> 43:08.616
She's the best thing in my life.

43:09.752 --> 43:11.811
I envy children.

43:11.888 --> 43:13.822
I envy their innocence.

43:14.891 --> 43:16.916
Yeah. Me too.

43:16.993 --> 43:18.853
<i>That's a Chinese thing, right?</i>

43:18.879 --> 43:19.747
<i>For stress. </i>

43:19.795 --> 43:21.729
Oh, that...

43:23.799 --> 43:26.233
just keeps me in the zone.

43:27.669 --> 43:30.228
Close-up magic.

43:30.304 --> 43:32.417
I bet your daughter loves that.

43:32.443 --> 43:33.696
<i>I don't know. </i>

43:35.276 --> 43:38.768
I guess I just mostly use it to entertain myself.

43:38.846 --> 43:40.939
<i>Listen,</i>

43:43.349 --> 43:46.750
could we, um, reschedule this for some other time?

43:46.820 --> 43:48.754
'Cause I haven't got much sleep.

43:48.822 --> 43:50.993
How about tomorrow at 10:00?

43:51.019 --> 43:52.646
Oh. Okay. Sure.

43:55.594 --> 43:57.619
Thank you.

43:57.696 --> 43:59.630
Take care, Detective.

44:05.470 --> 44:08.701
<i> Dr. Gregory said that he envied the innocence of children. </i>

44:08.773 --> 44:12.937
<i>But staring at the faces of a thousand missing kids,</i>

44:13.010 --> 44:15.739
<i>envy is the last thing you feel. </i>

44:15.812 --> 44:18.576
<i>All I felt was rage. </i>

44:19.916 --> 44:24.080
<i>Children are the only sacred thing left in this world. </i>

44:24.154 --> 44:26.986
<i>And most of these little ones were gone for good. </i>

44:27.056 --> 44:29.422
<i>But not the kid I was looking for. </i>

44:29.492 --> 44:32.086
<i>That child was still alive. </i>

44:32.161 --> 44:36.598
<i>If I could keep it that way, I knew it would
be the best thing I'd do in my lifetime. </i>

44:50.611 --> 44:52.176
Hey yourself, Detective.

44:52.202 --> 44:53.571
What's the problem?

44:57.484 --> 45:00.145
They found your snitch.

45:04.090 --> 45:07.313
I got three of my guys up there running around.

45:07.339 --> 45:08.882
All right, thanks.

45:10.929 --> 45:13.659
It's another fuckin' mess,

45:13.732 --> 45:15.666
just like you described it.

45:15.734 --> 45:17.861
Are you surprised?

45:17.936 --> 45:19.870
No, not really.

45:19.938 --> 45:21.808
- <i> You got two of those?</i>

45:21.834 --> 45:23.625
- <i> Yeah, here's one. </i>

45:24.742 --> 45:26.505
<i>Mark that "B."</i>

45:26.577 --> 45:30.206
<i>All right, everybody just, uh, just get out. </i>

45:40.690 --> 45:42.783
It's got a voice mail.

45:42.859 --> 45:46.453
You have one unheard voice message.

45:46.528 --> 45:47.477
Bernie, it's Terry.

45:47.503 --> 45:50.250
Listen, about the per... the thing we talked about...

45:50.299 --> 45:54.633
Find Mr. Parmaggi at a place called The
Crossing at the end of Old Mining Road.

45:54.703 --> 45:56.049
Now we're even, all right?

45:56.075 --> 45:57.992
After this, I don't owe you a dime.

45:58.039 --> 46:00.974
End of message.

46:02.143 --> 46:04.577
Doesn't this guy usually give us a finger?

46:04.645 --> 46:06.636
Yeah, but we ain't found one yet.

46:06.714 --> 46:09.204
- <i> The cash register. </i>
- What?

46:09.282 --> 46:12.683
It's in the fucking cash register!

46:17.057 --> 46:19.991
It was on the fucking videotape!

46:23.062 --> 46:25.690
Let's go, partner.

46:31.436 --> 46:34.599
<i>Maybe this guy just wants his box back. </i>

46:34.672 --> 46:38.233
No, that box was left in plain sight at the first murder scene.

46:38.309 --> 46:41.175
<i>If he wanted the box, he'd have it by now. </i>

46:41.245 --> 46:44.772
No, this figures for some kind of message.

46:44.848 --> 46:49.911
He's telling me if I keep looking for him
he's gonna kill that child, and I'll die too.

46:49.987 --> 46:52.887
Hunt for the Engineer, and the Engineer will hunt you.

46:52.955 --> 46:57.221
- What?
- He won't have to hunt for long, I can tell you that.

47:14.475 --> 47:16.739
You with me?

47:16.810 --> 47:18.903
Whatever you say, partner.

48:19.468 --> 48:22.061
Well, I see chips, but I...

48:22.136 --> 48:24.070
I don't see a cashier.

48:25.573 --> 48:27.507
You know where I can buy in?

48:29.777 --> 48:31.938
I'm looking for Mr. Parmaggi.

48:32.013 --> 48:33.843
Does he still work here?

48:33.914 --> 48:36.348
I do,

48:36.416 --> 48:39.385
and I know all the faces,

48:39.453 --> 48:42.388
though I can't say I remember yours.

48:42.456 --> 48:43.866
Those six-guns look real.

48:43.892 --> 48:45.415
Are you here to play?

48:47.159 --> 48:50.686
I have a permit for the guns, if you'd like to see it.

48:57.669 --> 48:59.796
Are you the Engineer?

49:00.872 --> 49:02.999
You flatter me, sir.

49:04.943 --> 49:06.876
Well,

49:06.944 --> 49:09.208
I'm not going away.

49:09.279 --> 49:12.214
You can tell him that. Okay?

49:12.282 --> 49:16.343
I got his message, and you can give him this message for me:

49:16.420 --> 49:20.856
I'm not gonna stop until I find that child... alive.

49:20.923 --> 49:22.857
I can assure you, Detective,

49:22.925 --> 49:27.589
you're quite mistaken about the Engineer's... message.

49:27.663 --> 49:30.426
Don't fuck with me.

49:30.499 --> 49:33.991
You like to play games, don't you, Detective?

49:34.069 --> 49:37.004
<i>The Engineer likes games,</i>

49:37.072 --> 49:41.508
and it appears that you're playing one of his games right now.

49:43.277 --> 49:46.974
He doesn't want you to stop.

49:47.047 --> 49:50.016
He wants you to play the game.

49:51.618 --> 49:54.553
You think this is a goddamn game?

51:06.420 --> 51:08.615
Tony?

51:53.429 --> 51:56.989
I'm still gonna find that child.

51:58.200 --> 52:00.134
That, I suspect,

52:00.202 --> 52:02.534
is the object of the game.

52:22.222 --> 52:25.589
<i> Joseph! Joe. </i>

52:27.727 --> 52:28.875
Holy shit.

52:28.901 --> 52:30.049
Come on.

52:41.439 --> 52:43.373
Turn it off.

52:43.441 --> 52:46.569
Turn it off!

52:46.644 --> 52:49.374
I've been trying to keep you conscious.

52:50.981 --> 52:51.982
Where are we going?

52:52.008 --> 52:52.961
<i>To the hospital.</i>

52:52.987 --> 52:54.271
<i>We're gettin'close. </i>

52:54.318 --> 52:55.115
I'm sorry, man.

52:55.141 --> 52:56.497
I got lost in the woods.

52:56.523 --> 52:57.904
I should have been there.

52:57.955 --> 53:00.788
- <i>Take me to the house. </i>
- What?

53:00.857 --> 53:02.501
Man, you gotta go to the hospital.

53:02.527 --> 53:03.372
You're fucked up.

53:03.426 --> 53:04.724
- <i>You could have a concussion. </i>

53:04.750 --> 53:06.215
- Just take me back to the squad!

53:15.570 --> 53:16.253
Joseph?

53:16.279 --> 53:18.325
I need to talk.

53:18.373 --> 53:20.568
Of course.
Please come in.

53:24.211 --> 53:25.030
Are you all right?

53:25.056 --> 53:26.602
Yeah, I think I'm losing it.

53:26.647 --> 53:28.293
Why don't you sit down?

53:28.319 --> 53:29.607
What do you mean?

53:29.650 --> 53:32.414
I think I'm going insane.

53:32.486 --> 53:36.012
That's a thought insane people rarely have.

53:36.089 --> 53:38.922
Joseph, please, sit down.

53:38.992 --> 53:43.088
I'm afraid if I sit down, I'm never gonna get up again.

53:47.299 --> 53:49.233
Years ago...

53:49.301 --> 53:51.769
when I was first on the force,

53:51.837 --> 53:55.329
I heard about somebody called the Engineer.

53:55.407 --> 53:57.398
I always thought it was just a...

53:57.476 --> 54:01.707
some campfire story to scare academy cadets and rookies.

54:01.779 --> 54:04.145
And then today,

54:04.215 --> 54:07.275
I heard his name again.

54:09.552 --> 54:12.544
You know what I'm talking about?

54:12.622 --> 54:14.784
Oh, please, continue what you were...

54:14.810 --> 54:16.174
Answer my question!

54:17.961 --> 54:20.554
What do you know about the Engineer?

54:51.825 --> 54:55.487
I've returned to this file many times.

54:55.561 --> 54:58.928
It was 1986, my first year as department counselor.

55:00.733 --> 55:03.702
He was a veteran like you, good at his job.

55:03.769 --> 55:06.601
Until he caught a case where everything led to one man...

55:06.671 --> 55:10.198
known only by his street name, the Engineer.

55:10.275 --> 55:14.371
This detective began to mistrust his own instincts.

55:15.947 --> 55:18.176
Self-doubt grew into paranoia.

55:18.248 --> 55:20.614
<i>And in his delusions,</i>

55:20.684 --> 55:23.983
<i>he elevated the Engineer into a figure of almost supernatural power. </i>

55:24.054 --> 55:28.251
He said the Engineer knew everything about every cop on the force,

55:28.324 --> 55:30.884
<i>especially him. </i>

55:30.960 --> 55:34.225
His anxiety rapidly shifted into a deep depression...

55:35.698 --> 55:39.394
till one day he came to work, sat down behind his desk...

55:40.736 --> 55:42.670
and shot himself in the head.

55:46.475 --> 55:49.171
What do you see there?

55:49.244 --> 55:52.838
The detective had it with him when he shot himself.

55:52.913 --> 55:56.781
I must admit that I was intrigued enough to actually go and look for it,

55:56.851 --> 55:59.251
<i>but when I checked the evidence archives,</i>

55:59.320 --> 56:01.412
it was gone.

56:01.488 --> 56:04.082
So it's probably either lost or destroyed by now.

56:04.157 --> 56:07.024
<i>All that's left of it is the picture. </i>

56:15.334 --> 56:17.131
What is it?

56:17.202 --> 56:19.975
<i>You couldn't get it out of your head.</i>

56:20.001 --> 56:21.459
<i>I think you know. </i>

56:23.375 --> 56:24.363
You're right.

56:24.389 --> 56:26.061
I did some research.

56:27.545 --> 56:30.105
It's called the Lament Configuration.

56:31.883 --> 56:34.976
It appears in occult literature here and there throughout the centuries.

56:35.051 --> 56:37.042
What do they say about it?

56:37.120 --> 56:41.056
<i>They say it's a window or a gateway. </i>

56:41.124 --> 56:43.058
You open it,

56:43.126 --> 56:46.720
they come for you and they tear you apart.

56:49.398 --> 56:51.332
"They"?

56:51.400 --> 56:52.717
Some call them Cenobites.

56:52.743 --> 56:55.691
Others call them demons and say they take you to hell.

56:55.738 --> 56:58.763
Well, they didn't take me to hell.

57:01.743 --> 57:03.231
You opened the box?

57:03.257 --> 57:05.135
<i>Yeah, last night. </i>

57:06.181 --> 57:09.581
I had some... nightmare,

57:09.650 --> 57:11.914
and...

57:11.985 --> 57:13.919
ever since then,

57:13.987 --> 57:16.182
I've been seeing...

57:17.491 --> 57:19.425
them.

57:22.361 --> 57:26.525
Am I going crazy?

57:28.267 --> 57:32.032
I'm more of a psychiatrist than I am a priest.

57:32.103 --> 57:36.130
Ask me if I believe in the devil, I don't know what to say.

57:36.208 --> 57:38.972
But ask me about this box,

57:39.044 --> 57:41.376
from what I've seen and read,

57:41.446 --> 57:43.379
I believe it's real.

57:43.447 --> 57:46.678
<i>But the history's consistent. </i>

57:46.750 --> 57:49.878
It opens, they come for you...

57:49.954 --> 57:51.888
and they leave.

57:51.956 --> 57:55.118
<i>So if you're saying they left you behind,</i>

57:55.191 --> 57:58.217
and you're still seeing them,

57:58.294 --> 58:00.489
then maybe they're still here.

58:08.804 --> 58:11.170
<i>I live in a world of facts,</i>

58:11.240 --> 58:13.504
<i>of close attention to detail. </i>

58:13.575 --> 58:15.838
<i>No matter how confusing the mystery,</i>

58:15.910 --> 58:18.208
<i>no matter how difficult the puzzle,</i>

58:18.279 --> 58:22.909
<i>the answer is always seen and the end is natural as rain. </i>

58:22.984 --> 58:26.852
<i>Everything... every process, no matter how complex,</i>

58:26.920 --> 58:29.184
<i>is a piece of reality in the end. </i>

58:29.256 --> 58:32.089
<i>And the design can be understood. </i>

58:32.158 --> 58:35.753
<i>All things can eventually be explained. </i>

58:35.829 --> 58:39.924
<i>But maybe some facts are in the eye of the beholder. </i>

58:39.999 --> 58:41.933
Mommy, wait!

58:42.001 --> 58:46.165
<i>And maybe some explanations are not of this world. </i>

58:46.238 --> 58:48.832
<i>Help me!</i>

59:04.788 --> 59:06.023
Where have you been?

59:06.049 --> 59:07.377
You've not called me.

59:07.403 --> 59:08.579
I have paged you.

59:08.625 --> 59:11.889
Told you I was working a case.

59:11.961 --> 59:15.294
Why do you keep lying to me, Joseph?

59:15.364 --> 59:18.094
You cannot keep doing this.
We...

59:18.167 --> 59:18.984
